        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 5:36PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 535 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles east of Nashoba to 9 miles southwest of
Octavia to 18 miles southwest of Hatfield to 12 miles west of Grannis
to 9 miles southwest of Vandervoort to 8 miles west of Wickes.
Movement was southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Plunketville, Smithville, Watson, Bethel, Battiest, Mount Herman, and
Sherwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
